Today is #crowpose in the #findyourflowchallenge & I cannot lie, I was not looking forward to this one. 
Everyone has that one pose that is the ultimate boss in a yogis quest to nail the classic asanas and for me, it has been crow pose. Mainly because my arm strength has always historically been weak so any arm balances make me a little nervous. 
I haven’t practiced this for a few weeks so when I first attempted I fell out very quickly & felt a little sad ☹️ 
This is when “fuck this shit I’m out” mode would have previously switched on and I would have retreated. However, I pulled myself together and tried again and again...and again until I managed to balance continuously for what felt like forever but was like 10 seconds. 
Remember what you see on here is a snapshot of the perfected post after a lot of practice and huffing and puffing. 
Wait 2 seconds for the video to see what I mean —->
Ps. I’m loving the real time videos now ❤️
