You may get into this pose either from Tadasana (mountain pose) by stepping one foot back or from Adho Mukha (Downward facing dog) by stepping the foot forward. 
Ideally, the knee is aligned over the ankle but if one experiences too much fatigue or discomfort in the knee area, The knee can be positioned backwards but never over the ankle.
The hips should remain square and not open in warrior one, spine lengthened and expands fully with each breath. Remember to let deep breaths guide your movements.
Warrior one aids in full chest and lungs expansion, Improves balance and stability and sends energy throughout the body.
How do you feel when you Practice this pose? Do you feel rooted, does it make you feel powerful? Do you experience any fatigue at all? Let me know in the comments.

